New Feature Ramen 👀👀🍜

@tokiwa_ramen has a new feature ramen bowl and it's definitely slurp worthy. Seafood Ramen packed with mussels, squid, scallop and shrimps all in tasty bowl of chicken broth w ginger and chewy noodles.

I love when they put out a new feature cause i've gone through this whole menu one too many times. As much as I love and will never go against my one true love, Goma Goma, this was a nice change to try 😊 Super clean flavour, peppery chicken broth and perfectly cooked seafood, definitely a good option if you're looking for something lighter!

Seafood Ramen • $19
Goma Goma • $16
Bou Gyoza • $6.5

@elcorazonyeg has definitely gained some points in my good books after this visit. 🤭 This new fusion Latin restaurant now open in Glenora offers creative dishes featuring a modern spin on Latin-American plates. Gluten free and vegetarian options offered as well!!

First of all there's 2 hour free parking in a lot behind the plaza (love to see it). Once you walk in, you're greeted by the kindest pals and welcomed into absolutely stunninggg spot. I immediately fell in love with the design of this space. Greenery, huge windows, tinted mirrors and just an overall great atmosphere that invites a warm yet sophisticated feel. 🌿

Let's talk drinks. Our waiter (great service btw) had killer recommendations and each drink was super unique and soooo yum. Love their Mojitos, especially the strawberry - sweet, citrusy and a bit of spice, the house made strawberry chili syrup was a super nice balance. The Vanilla Marg was also a big winner, shockingly a tasty balance of flavour. Every other drink was just as good, lots of variety, house made syrups, perfect combinations: you won't be disappointed with this Latin inspired, vibrant drink menu.

🌮Foooooood. I wanted to try everything on the menu. I feel like we got a good variety and feel for the menu. Offering up tapas, appies, salads/bowls, handhelds, entrees and more 🤭 Overall appies were top tier. Loved the ceviche, the ancho hot chicken is literally the most addicting *must try* dish. Same with the Tequenos, a classic dish, one of my favourites. Fish tacos were my fav. Blackened basa was recommended and surprised us with so much flavour. And alas, dessert. I'm not a sweets fan but these churros were 100% worth it. Great way to wrap up our meal 👏🏼

I'll definitely be back here for drinks, appies and a couple cheeky tacos. Date nights, lunch plans, special occasions - all a great idea to celebrate here at @elcorazonyeg 🙌🏼 Check 'em out! 

S/O @mitchelllawler for hand modelling 😆

El Corazon 📍14101 West Block Dr #yeg 
💸 Prices + Items -> Last Pic

Big appreciation post for my absolute favourite spot in the city 🤍

@izakayatomo recently celebrated their 10Y anniversary and invited myself, plus a handful of their biggest supporters 🤭 So much sushi, so much sake. (like.. a lot of sake 🫣)

I can't even express the gratitude I have for everyone at Tomo. The fact that they invited customers they know who have been supporting them the most is just beyond me. The first time I walked into this place- I knew immediately this was gonna be my spot. So warm, inviting and just overall the absolute best vibe. Not only do they have the best sushi in the city (and i stand by that), but they also give a shit. They care, it shows in the way they treat customers, the quality of their ingredients and the dishes they make. More businesses should take a page out of Tomo's book. 

We got to see first hand all the amazing fish they get and all the slick knife skills. It was my absolute heaven seeing all my favourite eats in such a large quantity 🥹 Food coma was definitely achieved.

If you haven't stopped by and think you like sushi but you're still eating low quality, grocery store sushi - do better, treat yourself. It's a better life with tomo 😏

TOMO FOREVER 👏🏼👏🏼
(also shoutout to Chris and Terry for always welcoming and putting up with my shenanigans over these years 🤍)

location.city_name: 백정 에드먼튼 - Baekjeong Korean BBQ House

social_posts.post_text:
The best KBBQ in town 🍖🔥

By faaaar @baekjeong_edmonton is the best spot for all your korean BBQ needs. For those of you who don't know, KBBQ is grilling your own cuts of meat on a hot grill. The best part is being able to cook everything to your own preference. PLUS they have a button at each table so service is always great cause you can just tap the button at anytime.

You can go the al a crate route or order one of their combos. Personally I don't do combos, I like to pick and choose which cuts I personally like (and the fancy ones 🙈). All orders also include bottomless house made side salads, kimchis, condiments, and seasonings which is nice cause who doesn't love free sides?? I always eat my weight in the kimchi and onions cause they're just way too good. My all time fav cut of meat was the B3. Kkochgalbisal (aka boneless sliced beef short rib) ugh so worth every penny. 

The food quality was nothing short of perfect. All the meats are always flavourful and juicy. Mmm juicy meat 👀  I'm telling ya, hands down this is the best spot. It definitely can add up price wise but you 100% get your moneys worth with how high quality everything is. ALSO I went on a weekday and compared to the other times I went on weekends, I highly recommend going on a weekday if you can. Everything was just better and didn't feel so rushed.

Overall, Baekjeong Korean BBQ is a great choice if you're looking for super high quality cuts of meat and a fun, hands on experience! Only huge downside is $$$$ but worth it 🙌🏼💸

A12. Dak-gangjeong $24.95
B3. Kkochgalbisal $36
B5. Kkochdeungsim $35
B9. Useol $30
P4. Yangnyeom Dwaeji-galbi $25
M16. Yukhoe Bibimbab $21.95

Happy new year pals 🎉  #topnine 

Just wanted to say that i'm so thankful to have this little foodie community. Everyone who's stopped to say hi or who i've met through this page being alive, to all the amazing owners who pour their life into their passion and allow us to enjoy it, you guys make life better, even if it's just for a moment. ✨

One thing that was never really talked about it why this page exists. Didn't notice no one really knew until people around me started asked how/why it started. This is a bit tough to put out but a few close homies told me I should be talking about it since so many people struggle with this. Still def makes me feel so vulnerable and weird but 🤷🏼‍♀️

(TW: this does go a bit deep, but dw it's in the past)
So initially this page was a public page (which only my friends and family knew about) that held me accountable to cook and go out to eat. This is because I spent majority of my teenage years dealing with anorexia. It was a tough, life draining point in my life. I had a moment where I was very very close to not being around anymore due to my weight. I realized that this isn't the outcome I wanted, I was just young and insecure. So yeg.menu was born and in the first year it blew up. Never expected any of it to happen, but I loved doing it cause it finally felt like I wasn't alone. After awhile I felt a new relationship with food, it was no longer a fear but now a way to bring people together, enjoy new flavours and something I couldn't get to experience for so many years. Because of you guys always supporting and sending me DMs, etc, you guys in a way became my support system 😌 I felt this sense of community and a feeling of support that I didn't have before. 4 years going strong and in the healthiest state i've ever been in 🥹 One year of so many trips, new friends, old friends, fun times and of course ALLLL the food.

Thank you truly, you may think this is just hobby, but it's way bigger to me and you guys play a huge part. Shoutout to all the amazing local spots that allowed me to enjoy food again 🥰  To another happy, healthy year 🤍 (and support ur homies!!!)

iykyk @taubayyeg 

Being a foodie is definitely harder in this weather because all I truly want everyday is soup 🍲 (and side beef meatballs since they’re so tasty but also ✨more broth✨) + definitely order their chili oil, it's a must.

Been coming to this spot for years and it will always have a special place in my heart. Hidden away downtown behind macewan in an unsuspecting street is the most authentic and satisfying boiling bowl of pho you'll get in this city. 
Good soup☑️ Parking☑️ Cheap☑️
Good prices(two people can easily eat for ~$25), amazing broth that still can't be beat, and the ingredients are always high quality. Prices did go up since before but what hasn't these days so it's totally understandable.

If you haven't been to @taubayyeg then you really gotta change that homie, figure it out 🤦🏼‍♀️ And hopefully they're open when you go 😂

Well after seeing all these "look we got invited and ate free food!! sOoOo gOood" posts - I too got invited. Did I go? No 😂 Cause i'm always sceptical of those reviews. But inevitably curiosity got to me so I caved in and they took care of us.(points for us missing the grand media open cause still got food but didn't have to wait in an obnoxiously long line with a bunch of influencers lmao)

My expectations were not high at all. I do love getting the cheese dog from hmart so I was pretty excited and had to see what @chungchun.ca was all about. 

Surprisingly, actually not bad. I'm a fiend for cheese + anything korean and this spot definitely ups the ante on corn dogs. Their menu only focuses on korean style hot dogs as well as non-meat options. The rice flour they use is really nice too, breading 10/10, it's got a really nice chew and the coating adds a really good crunch. You'll probably find one you like with the tons of options and sauces they have.

That being said, it's still just fried and battered cheese and meat with seasoning and sauce 😂 I loved it (except the ramen topping🫣) and we ate all five but it definitely is a hefty snack that isn't exactly the first choice if you're on the healthy route. Is it the most amazing thing i've ever had? Nah. Is it over hyped? Probably. But it's just a higher quality "fancier" than your average, corn dog hehe

Worth trying at least once tho, even tho they really don't look like the most amazing lol, good flavour cause you know... fried cheese and meat 😂 

Prices range: ~$5-$8

social_posts.post_text:

WOOD-FIRE BRUNCH 🥂🍳🔥

For @bravenrestaurant brunch is not just a meal, it's an experience. & Braven knows how to make it fancy af. From the decadent Braven Wagyu & eggs to the crisp brunch nachos, we were in brunch heaven. And their variety of bevy's + crafted cocktails like The Duchess and French 75 are the perfect pair. Fancy brunch achieved 🙌🍳🥂 #bravenyeg

With tastefully modern decor, with clean lines and elegant touches. Paired w/ friendly, knowledgeable staff that are always ready to make your brunch experience a memorable one. 

Lets talk FOOOOD. Buckle up cause first up, the Braven Wagyu & Eggs. This dish is an absolute game-changer. WAGYU FOR BRUNCH? Hello yes PLEASE. The juicy and flavourful Wagyu beef is perfectly paired with perfect eggs, savoury roasted tomato, crispy sourdough and every bite = top tier.

For something out of the norm, Brunch Nachos. On paper this would not be my first choice but they brought it out for us and I have zero regrets. Featuring CRISSSSP tortilla chips loaded up with queso fresco, jalapenos, pico & pickled red onion. It's a snacky dish that is almost too good to share.

If you're in the mood for something a little more savory, one of my favs: Mushroom Flatbread. This dish features a crispy flatbread topped truffled duxelles, wild & tame mushrooms, spinach, grilled onion. It's the perfect veggie option.

To wash it all down, make sure to try the Duchess. Rose infused gin, pinot grigio, lavender syrup, lemon and vanilla. Sorry mimosa's, you've been outshined this time. It's light, refreshing, and the perfect way to complement any dish on the menu. And if you're in the mood for something a little more classic, try the French 75.

Overall, if you're looking for a brunch experience that will make your wallet cry and that's both indulgent and down-to-earth. With delicious food, expertly crafted cocktails, and a warm and welcoming atmosphere, Braven is the spot to be.

Huge thank you to @bravenrestaurant for the invite, had the cutest brunch date w mum! 💕
Brunch is available every sunday woooo!

Brunch Nachos • $18
Bacon, egg, cheese flatbread • $26
Mushroom flatbread • $19
Wagyu & eggs • MP
S'mores pancake • $24

And if you really want to experience the pinnacle of breakfast sandwiches, you gotta try their Grick. This sandwich is everything you'd want in a breakfast sandwich. It's got all the goods - bacon, egg, cheese, and rosemary aioli, tomato jam & arugula - all nestled between a soft bun. It's like a breakfast sandwich on steroids. So if you're ready to grow tf up and looking for a sandwich that will change your life, hop on over to Farrow. 😤😤🔥 fr fr on god 🥵

@italiancentreshop has been serving up an extensive selection of imported goods and personally my go-to = their delicious pizza.

The pizza dough is made in-house daily and results in the perfect crust. Their toppings range from classics we all know and love as well as rotating features! 🎉

My current fav is the Boscaiola(#10) which is dressed with bechamel sauce, mozzarella, a variety of mushrooms, truffle oil, and italian speck. It's a heavenly combination of creamy, cheesey, salty from the speck, earthy mushrooms, and fragrant truffle oil. This za makes me the happiest.

I've been loving their portuguese tarts as well, they're always so perfect, had to buy a whole box of them 💁🏼‍♀️

#10 Boscaiola • $18

Forever my one true love 🤍🍜

Alright, buckle up homies and grab your chopsticks. @tokiwa_ramen has my whole fricken heart. Tbh if you haven't been at this point after i've constantly praised them the last 4 years, you reeeeeally gotta step up your game.

Tokiwa doesn't mess around when it comes to freshness and S-tier quality. Every broth is simmered for hours to perfection, the noodles are cooked just right every time, and the toppings are just a classic. The menu offers something for everyone, with a vegetarian option and (if you wanna be that weirdo) they have rice bowls as well. 

Personally, I'm a simp for the Goma Goma. After going through the entire menu, I always have gone back to the goma. I've had it way too many times and I still crave it every day. This bowl of heaven is rich, flavorful, and downright addictive. Let's talk about the broth(btw!! you can get broth refills if you're a soup fiend like me). This bowls got a creamy sesame base that's been simmered for ten hours, giving it a nutty and slightly sweet flavor. The noodles are bouncy, and firm, the exact al dente to soak up all that yummy broth. I could drink gallons of their broth fr fr. Top that off with chopped pork, wood ear mushrooms, a jammy ramen egg, bean sprouts, bok choy, crisp lotus root and green onion, drizzle of chili oil and you're vibin'.

The atmosphere is slick and clean. Staff is always on point so don't worry if you're new to the ramen game, they will guide you through the menu. From 11am-3pm they're slaying the ramen game. The only downside is that they sell out of soup so your ramen enjoying window is short since they usually close early.

So go get your noodle fix.
Cause I've met way too many ppl who haven't been and it hurts my heart. Y'all can do better than that, treat yooooself.

Goma Goma • $17
All ramen bowls are $16-$17.50

But let's be real, you're gonna want to eat all the sushi. And we're not just talking one or two rolls here - we're talking a full-on sushi marathon. It's like the sushi is calling to you, begging you to eat more. And who are you to say no?

Sure, you might feel like a beached whale after your meal, but it's totally worth it. You'll leave with a full belly and a smile on your face(and maybe your belt loosened up like i do lmao)

So, if you're in the mood for some seriously delicious sushi and don't mind the inevitable food coma that comes with it, head on over to Sushi Toshi. For a price of $35/40 you can feast your little heart out.

Brunchin' it up over at @workshopeatery 🙌🏼

This spots an absolute classic, it was actually the first brunch spot I went to and had my first benny🍳 And this benny was bomb as heck, for $23 you can get a feature brunch, this case it was a lox benny braised in beets which we loved. Paired that with a $11 mimosa or a $5.75 cappuccino 🍾☕️

Definitely a place you wanna check out for your next sunday brunch date ☀️

AYOO WHAT'S POPPIN'? The newest latin inspired spot to hit downtown 😎

@eljardinyeg : "Influenced by International Latin flavours to offer a unique dining experience with vibrant cocktails, adventurous wine list, craft and international beers which compliment our inspired food." LOOK AT THE VARIETY OF DISHES SHEEEEESH😵🔥

& lemme tell ya, they delivered. The cocktails were BOMB and the food was so yums and paired with unique flavours for each dish🙏🏼

I highlyyyyyyy recommend the gouda tequenos(my personal fav and the best tequenos i've ever had), chorizo a la sidra. Their ceviche is also bombs 🙌🏼

CHECK EM OUT😍

Tried that new new waygu carpaccio feature from @cactusclubcafe when we headed down for happy hour 🤩🥩

Flavourful, light and satisfying - i'd say worth trying at least once especially if you have never tried wagyu, Cactus is definitely an easy and accessible spot to try it!

As for happy hour, cmon we all know they kill it. I'm obsessed with their fries, mini crispy chicken sandwiches, rigatoni bolognese and new to my HH go to; aburi salmon roll! (and of course the cocktails 🥂😎)

What's your go to?

Something to definitely right home about ✨

When quality meets flavour, @izakayatomo is just always on top of their game and absolutely never have and never will disappoint 💁🏼‍♀️ Tomo and his team sling out some of the BEST izakaya dishes and sushi you can get here in #yeg . 

Whenever i'm craving sushi and need my fix (which is very very often lol) - @izakayatomo is always my go to.

Check em out ➡️ @izakayatomo

location.city_name: Glasshouse Kitchen Bar at the Enjoy Centre

social_posts.post_text:
Brunch is always a good idea ☀️

@glasshousekitchenbaratenjoy has been our go to brunch spot for yearssss and they never disappoint 🥞☕️🍳 

Over the years we've just seen them improve day by day and never slip up, they sling out a small high quality menu every weekend. Their menu is a delicious blend of brunch classics we all know n love, as well as unique fares fit for the out the brunch norm box ppl. 
From favs to a variety of benedicts to bowls to toasts, there's really an option for everyone.(and of course cocktails 🍾🥂) Plus the atmosphere is unbeatable, trust me you'll never wanna leave ☀️

All their eggs are locally sourced and all their bread is make in house 👏🏼 As a scratch kitchen you can always expect yummy eats made with care 🥰 Plus, being in the enjoy centre sharing space with other local spots, they get all their specialty oils and balsamic from @evoolution104 next door! 

Never time you wanna brunch it up, I highly recommend moseying on over to @glasshousekitchenbaratenjoy to get your fix (while also supporting local woooo!)

A few of my go to's ⤵️
